This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of graph analysis and visualization techniques could also suggest sub-categories such as Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper's focus on language biases and cross-lingual analysis could suggest sub-categories such as Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD) or Computer Systems Organization (cs.CY).
